  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "A network protocol is a set of standards and rules that govern how 2+ devices communicate",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "over a network (a standardised way of doing certain actions and formatting data).",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Remember",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "OSI",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "OSI",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "OSI stands for Open Systems Interconnection. It is a conceptual model created by the International",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Organization of Standardization and enables di- verse communication systems to communicate using standard protocols.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The OSI model does not perform any functions in the networking process, it just divides network",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "communication into 7 abstraction layers, so it is seen as a universal language for computer networking.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The layers, going from lowest to highest are:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Physical",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Data Link",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Network",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Transport",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Session",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Presentation",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Application",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In the OSI model, layers 1-4 are considered the lower layers, and mostly concern themselves",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "with moving data around. Layers 5-7 are considered the upper layers, containing application-level data.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Physical-Layer",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Physical Layer",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The lowest layer of the OSI model, concerned with electrically\/optically transmitting raw unstructured",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "data bits across the network from the physical layer of the sending device to the physical layer of",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the receiving device.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "It can include specifications such as voltages, pin layout, cabling, and radio frequencies.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Physical resources, such as network hubs, cabling, repeaters, network adapters or modems; like RS-232 and",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "RJ45, 100ASE-TX reside in this layer.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Data-Link-Layer",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Data Link Layer",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "At the data link layer, directly connected nodes are used to perform node-to-node data transfer where",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "data is packaged into frames. It also corrects errors that may have occurred at the physical layer.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The data link layer encompasses two sub-layers of its own.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The first is media access control (MAC), which provides flow control and multiplexing for device",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "transmissions over a network.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The second sub-layer is local link control (LLC), which provides flow and error control over the physical",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "medium as well as identifies link proto- cols, like Ethernet, 802.11, Wifi 7, Fibre Channel, Frame Relay,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and Token Ring.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Network-Layer",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Network Layer",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The network layer is responsible for receiving frames from the data link layer, and delivering them to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "their intended destinations based on the addresses contaiend inside the frame.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "It finds the destination using logical addresses, such as internet protocol. Routers are a crucial",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "component used to quite literally route information where it needs to go between networks.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "IP, ARP, IPsec, ICMP, IGMP, OSPF all reside here",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Transport-Layer",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Transport Layer",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This layer manages the delivery and error checking of data packets, regulating the size, sequencing",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and ultimately, the transfer of data between systems and hosts.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Examples of the transport layer include TCP, aka ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Transmission Control Protocol",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : "; UDP, SCTP, SSL, and TLS.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Internet-Protocol-Suite",
          "level" : 4,
          "text" : "Internet Protocol Suite",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Transmission Control Protocol\/Internet Protocol, aka Internet Protocol Suite, is the set of protocols",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "used over the internet.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "It organises how data packets are communicated and makes sure packets have the following information:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Source - Which computer the message came from",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Destination - Where should the message go",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Packet sequence - The order the message data should be re-assembled",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Data - Self explanatory much?",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Error check - The check to verify the message has been transmitted correctly.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "TCP\/IP Protocol includes:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Transfers web pages from web servers to client.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "All webpage addresses start with http, and a https address is a secure web address which has",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "been encrypted. The latter is used for sites holding secure information, like bank details.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "FTP (File Transfer Protocol)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "A way to download, upload, and transfer files from one location to another on the Internet",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "and between computer systems. Often used for organising files on a web server for a website.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "You can have private access to an area on an FTP server where you can upload your files. You",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "can then give another user access to download the documents that you have shared.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "UDP (User Datagram Protocol)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "A communications protocol pri- marily used to establish low-latency and loss-tolerating connections",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "between applications on the internet.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Similar to TCP, but messages are sent as chunks instead of packets, it is often faster, allowing",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "for gaming\/video calls over the internet.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Although transfers are faster, they are not guaranteed.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Consider the following: TCP and UDB are required to put a baby (data) into a crib (destination).",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "TCP slowly, but carefully places the baby into the crib, whereas UDP dropkicks the baby through a",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "field goal, through the window, into the crib, which has a larger chance of the baby getting a severe",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "concussion (data corruption).",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "SMTP (Simple Mail Transfer Protocol)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "An Internet standard communication protocol for electronic mail transmission over a network to a mail server.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "IMAP\/POP3 (Internet Message Access Protocol, Post Office Protocol)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "governs retrieving emails from email servers.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "IMAP is an Internet standard protocol used by email clients to retrieve email messages from a mail",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "server over a TCP\/IP connection.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "POP3 is an older protocol that was originally designed to be used on only one computer. Unlike modern",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "protocols that use two-way syn- chronization, POP3 only supports one-way email synchronization, only",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "allowing users to download emails from a server to a client.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Advantages of IMAP include access on multiple devices, synchro- nisation, ability to download parts,",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "and this is because mail is stored in the server.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Disadvantages of IMAP include computational overhead, privacy and performance.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "The advantages of POP3 are the disadvantages of IMAP, and vice versa. POP3 downloads mail from the server",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "to the client and deletes the mail from the server.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "VOIP (Voice over Internet Protocol, aka IP telephony)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "A method and group of technologies for voice calls for the delivery of voice communication sessions",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "over IP networks, such as the Internet.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Advantages include lower costs, completely portable, advanced fea- tures and are more scalable than",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : " ",
                              "type" : "text"
                            },
                            {
                              "text" : "telephone lines.",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Session-Layer",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Session Layer",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The session layer controls the conversations between different computers.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A session or connection between machines is set up, managed, and terminated at layer 5.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Session layer services also include authentication and reconnections. E.g. Session establishment in TCP, SIP, RTP.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Presentation-Layer",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Presentation Layer",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This layer formats\/translates data for the application layer based on the syn- tax or semantics",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "that the application accepts.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Hence, it is also called the syntax layer. It also handles encryption and decryption required by the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "application layer, such as HTML, DOC, JPEG, MP3, M4V, and Sockets.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Application-Layer",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Application Layer",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "At this layer, both the end user and application layer interact directly with the software application.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This layer sees network services provided to end-user applications such as a web browser or Office 365.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The application layer identifies communication partners, resource availability, and synchronizes",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "communication. E.g. DNS, WWW\/HTTP. P2P EMAIL\/POP, SMTO, Telnet FTP",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
